> @stephenxs can you please confirm warmboot sonic-mgmt test is passing with this change as well?

@liat-grozovik Passed on Spectrum and Spectrum 3 platforms. I didn't test it on Spectrum 2 platform as there isn't an available test bed.
This is not platform independent so I think it's safe for warm reboot.

> this seems to be having the similar changes in PR #1521. Is this the superset?

Yes, this is incremental development on top of https://github.com/Azure/sonic-swss/pull/1521. When https://github.com/Azure/sonic-swss/pull/1521 is merged, we can see the incremental part clearly.

https://github.com/Azure/sonic-swss/pull/1521 fixes the sub interface removal sequence.
```
        if (getIntfIpCount(alias))
        {
            return false;
        }
```
Before change in https://github.com/Azure/sonic-swss/pull/1521, `getIntfIpCount(alias)` checks parent port ip count not sub port ip count, for sub port interface removal.

